{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|かんなぎ}}

{{IPAchar|/kamunaɡi/}} → {{IPAchar|/kaɴnaɡi/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=かんなぎ|-}}. Originally a compound of {{compound|ja|sort=かんなぎ|神|tr1=kamu|t1=god, spirit|和ぎ|tr2=nagi|t2=calming, calming down}}, the {{m|ja|連用形||tr=ren'yōkei|continuative or stem form}} of verb {{m|ja|和ぐ|tr=nagu||to become calm, to become quiet}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

{{ja-noun|かんなぎ}}

# {{lb|ja|sort=かんなぎ|archaic}} a [[medium]] or [[shaman]], usually female, who acts as a [[medium]] between humans and the [[spirit]]s or [[god]]s, helping to communicate between the two and to [[calm]] any supernatural or spiritual [[upset]]
#: {{synonyms|ja|巫女|tr1=miko|神子|tr2=miko|神子|tr3=kanko}}

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|こうなぎ}}

{{IPAchar|/kamunaɡi/}} → {{IPAchar|/kaũnaɡi/}} → {{IPAchar|/kaunaɡi/}} → {{IPAchar|/kɔːnaɡi/}} → {{IPAchar|/koːnaɡi/}}

Shift in pronunciation of the {{m|ja|神|tr=kamu}} element, similar to the pattern seen in terms such as {{m|ja|神戸||Kōbe}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

{{ja-noun|こうなぎ|hhira=かうなぎ}}

# {{lb|ja|sort=こうなぎ|archaic|possibly|_|obsolete}} a [[medium]] or [[shaman]], usually female, who acts as a [[medium]] between humans and the [[spirit]]s or [[god]]s, helping to communicate between the two and to [[calm]] any supernatural or spiritual [[upset]]
#: {{synonyms|ja|巫女|tr1=miko|神子|tr2=miko|神子|tr3=kanko}}
